I"w<p>Cryptocurrency has seen dramatic growth since its inception in 2009. Around 16% of American adults have invested in cryptocurrencies. In theme with prior executive orders advancing US cyber policy, the White House recently signed <a href="https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/statements-releases/2022/03/09/fact-sheet-president-biden-to-sign-executive-order-on-ensuring-responsible-innovation-in-digital-assets/">an executive order on cryptocurrencies and other digital assets</a>. Crypto enthusiasts view this as a win, but what does ensuring the responsible development of digital asset mean for the average American?</p>
